# Component Structure Convention

All components in `components/` directories must follow this standardized folder structure.

## Required Files

Each component must have its own folder with PascalCase naming:

```
ComponentName/
├── index.ts                    # Re-exports (required)
├── ComponentName.tsx           # Main component (required)
├── ComponentName.unit.tsx      # Unit tests (required)
├── ComponentName.stories.tsx   # Storybook documentation (required)
├── ComponentName.module.css    # CSS modules styling (required)
└── ComponentName.llm.md        # LLM documentation (design-system only)
```

## File Purposes

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `index.ts` | Export the component and its types for clean imports |
| `ComponentName.tsx` | Main component implementation with TypeScript interface |
| `ComponentName.unit.tsx` | Vitest unit tests covering all functionality |
| `ComponentName.stories.tsx` | Storybook stories showcasing variants and states |
| `ComponentName.module.css` | Scoped CSS using CSS Modules |
| `ComponentName.llm.md` | Documentation optimized for AI/LLM consumption |

## Naming Conventions

- **Folder name**: PascalCase (e.g., `ExampleButton`, `UserCard`)
- **File names**: Match folder name with appropriate extension
- **Component export**: Named export matching the component name
- **Props interface**: `{ComponentName}Props`

## Export Pattern

```tsx
// index.ts
export { ComponentName } from "./ComponentName";
export type { ComponentNameProps } from "./ComponentName";
```

## Barrel File

Components should be re-exported from `src/components/index.ts`:

```tsx
// src/components/index.ts
export * from "./ComponentName";
export * from "./AnotherComponent";
```

## Creating New Components

Use the PlopJS generator to scaffold new components:

```bash
pnpm generate:component
```

This automatically creates all required files and updates the barrel export.
